## 4. План реализации

### Phase A (этот TZ) — CSS Foundations (Layer 1)

**Файлы:**
- `frontend/src/styles.css` — добавить 3 utility-класса + JSDoc.

**Шаги:**

1. **A.1** Добавить `.pi-tech-label` как `@utility` (Tailwind v4 syntax):
```css
/**
 * .pi-tech-label — 10px monospace tech label.
 *
 * Use for: REF numbers, IDs, metadata in corners of structural panels.
 * Contrast: AAA (8.0:1 light, 7.5:1 dark) via --color-muted-foreground-strong.
 * NOT for body text — too small for paragraphs.
 */
@utility pi-tech-label {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 10px;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  color: var(--color-muted-foreground-strong);
  line-height: 1;
}
```

2. **A.2** Добавить `.pi-corner-marks` как `@layer components` (CSS-only via pseudo-elements):
```css
@layer components {
  /**
   * .pi-corner-marks — 8px L-shaped corner marks for structural panels.
   *
   * Adds architectural blueprint feel via two ::before/::after pseudo-elements
   * forming L-shapes in top-left and bottom-right corners. Pure CSS, no DOM pollution.
   * Pointer-events: none ensures no click-blocking on inner controls.
   *
   * Use for: empty states, structural cards, showcase panels.
   * NOT for: active interactive panels (use hairline border instead).
   */
  .pi-corner-marks {
    position: relative;
  }
  .pi-corner-marks::before,
  .pi-corner-marks::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .pi-corner-marks::before {
    top: -1px;
    left: -1px;
    border-right: none;
    border-bottom: none;
  }
  .pi-corner-marks::after {
    bottom: -1px;
    right: -1px;
    border-left: none;
    border-top: none;
  }
}
```

3. **A.3** Добавить `.pi-dashed-panel` как `@utility`:
```css
/**
 * .pi-dashed-panel — 1px dashed panel for empty states and draft-style surfaces.
 *
 * Honest "blueprint" feel: shows the panel is a draft or empty container.
 * Use for: PiEmptyState, draft cards, "no data" placeholders.
 * NOT for: active panels with content (use hairline border instead).
 *
 * Contrast: dashed border has lower perceived contrast than solid,
 * so use ONLY on near-empty surfaces where the border is decorative.
 */
@utility pi-dashed-panel {
  border: 1px dashed var(--color-rule);
  background-color: transparent;
}
```

4. **A.4** Verify: `cd frontend && pnpm exec tsc -p tsconfig.app.json --noEmit` exit 0.

5. **A.5** Visual verify на `/kit/playground`:
   - Создать test-fixture HTML с каждым из 3 utilities.
   - Browser-use: Light + Dark mode, screenshot, check console errors = 0.
   - Verify contrast: `.pi-tech-label` text via DevTools computed style.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- 3 utility-класса доступны в `styles.css`.
- Frontend typecheck: 0 errors.
- Browser visual verify: Light + Dark, no console errors.
- Никаких regressions в существующих 24+ компонентах.
- `verify-status.sh` FAIL count unchanged.

---

## 5. Риски и tradeoff

| Риск | Вероятность | Митигация |
|---|---|---|
| A11y regression: `.pi-tech-label` при 10px даёт AAA только при `--color-muted-foreground-strong` | Низкая | Bind строго к `var(--color-muted-foreground-strong)` (8.0:1 light, 7.5:1 dark). JSDoc запрещает override. |
| Visual noise: `.pi-corner-marks` over-applied → «1990s hacker terminal» look | Средняя | Phase 2 (TZ-94) gating: explicit list компонентов для adoption. Без `.pi-corner-marks` в production-страницах до TZ-94. |
| Naming convention drift: `.pi-*` vs Tailwind utilities | Низкая | Все 3 utilities префиксованы `pi-` (Paper & Ink convention per TZ-90A). JSDoc объясняет scope. |
| `.pi-dashed-panel` контраст ниже solid `hairline` | Средняя | Dashed border perceptual contrast ~1.1:1 (ниже solid 1.3:1). Применять ТОЛЬКО на near-empty surfaces. JSDoc предупреждает. |
| Tabular-nums не работает в Firefox < 34 | Negligible | Tailwind v4 baseline — Firefox 34+ (2014). Project поддерживает modern browsers only. |
| Phase 1 без adopters → utilities мертвы до TZ-94 | Средняя | Phase 1 ships utilities + `/kit/playground` showcase fixture. TZ-94 ships adopters. Phase 3 (TZ-95) ships showcase. |

---

